cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it proposes a new method for document summarization using pre-training of transformer sentence encoders. Additionally, the paper uses the CNN/Dailymail and New York Times datasets, which are commonly used in NLP research. It could also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) because of the use of neural networks and the focus on improving performance through pre-training. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Neural Networks (cs.NE) are also possible sub-categories due to the focus on document summarization and the use of neural networks for encoding and summarization.
